_aChangeLog.text: Fix an obscure bug with the cutscene where people who are spectating can pick up items.

_aLatestUpdates._sText: The link for the stripper fix is right here.

_aChangeLog.text: Added a new zombie item called Aether "Cybernetic Rage". This item buffs the zombie's within 768 units speed temporarily by 2x but sets their HP to 1000 HP except the user itself. This HP will not get overridden from the AFK teleport protection until the speed effect has finished. The speed effect can be overridden by Aether Electric Field Generators and Aether Light Cannons. Cooldown for the item is 120s (75s if no EntWatch).

The Intro Camera Sequence is disabled by default. It can be re-enabled by adding the optional stripper included in the .zip file. (Make sure you have CSSFixes in your server to make sure it does not soft-lock your players)
Fixed the Fire Launcher projectile spawning more fire fields than usual when multiple zombies are hit in one spot causing huge amounts of damage.
Fixed Soundscapes not getting packed in from last version.
Made the final afk teleport in the ending start from 1 minute left (from 30 seconds left)
Added decorations to some parts of the map
Moved the crates in "Stairs in Room #3 Before Elevator". Hopefully nerfing bunnyhopping.

2 AFK Teleport Areas now have a bullet blocking shield that makes zombies able to go out without getting shot to a corner. Items still can pass through this shield. These shields are present on the following AFK Teleports: (After Elevator, After Tram)
Applied optional stripper fixes from last version.

_aLatestUpdates._sText: The optional stripper file to enable the Intro Cutscene Sequence is included in the zip file.

_sText:
"Aether Supplies Inc. has a goal, and their goals are to sell weapons of destruction to anyone with malicious intents. Infiltrate one of their airships and blow the airship up to avoid this reality from happening."

Map by Pasas1345
Svarog Model from Honkai: Star Rail (Hoyoverse)

Music List:
Context Sensitive - Portlight
Context Sensitive - Mask
Context Sensitive - Intel
Context Sensitive - Trouble
HoyoMix - Wildfire

Experiments with better lighting and cubemaps and a defense oriented map turned into this map. More decorated than the other maps I have published... maybe.

Includes
  • 1 Long Defense Map
  • Intro Cutscene (with a case of soft-locking if you do a specific set of actions)
  • 1 Boss
  • 4 Types of Items
  • Random Item Spawns
  • Scenic Ending

Hope you enjoy the map!
